# Public metrics endpoint exposed by the fast-auth-metrics-dashboard.
# Drives the landing's /Live Network/ panel (lib/metrics.ts → app/page.tsx).
# /status auto-derives its data URL from this same origin (lib/status.ts),
# so setting FASTAUTH_METRICS_URL is enough — no need to set both.
#
# - Dev: defaults to http://localhost:3000/api/public/metrics if unset, so
#   running the dashboard alongside on :3000 just works.
# - Production: REQUIRED. Point at the deployed dashboard, e.g.
#     FASTAUTH_METRICS_URL=https://fast-auth-metrics-dashboard.vercel.app/api/public/metrics
#   If unset, /Live Network/ shows "Live data unavailable" and /status falls
#   back to a placeholder banner.
FASTAUTH_METRICS_URL=

# Optional override — only needed if /status should pull from a different
# host than /metrics. Falls back to FASTAUTH_METRICS_URL's origin otherwise.
# FASTAUTH_STATUS_URL=
